      {
        "id": "0a009fd38afbbbe9d02f21973a6c9ed0e924d0da",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 93,
          "name": "Vijay Venkatesh Kumar",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "vijayv81@gmail.com",
          "username": "vv770d"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-06-14 17:03:12.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1\n\nI don't see blueprint-generator/version.properties  updated (should be 1.1.0 to match pom version). \n\nJess - The version is set as build arg in the jjb.\n      - '{project-name}-{stream}-{subproject}-release-version-java-daily':\n            version-properties: 'blueprint-generator/version.properties'\n\nI assume this will still be required under new build job.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "8f76949612755924e4f05883e9431af0762b03fb",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 481,
          "name": "Jessica Wagantall",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jwagantall@linuxfoundation.org",
          "username": "jwagantall"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-06-14 17:06:31.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nOh.. interesting.. \nThe global-jjb assumes the version.properties is in the root of the repo. \nCan we move it there?",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "f95d6ab73ea92246bd49082db75cc9705d649520",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 93,
          "name": "Vijay Venkatesh Kumar",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "vijayv81@gmail.com",
          "username": "vv770d"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-06-14 17:27:05.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nThis project host both python (which required disabling nexus-staging-maven-plugin) and java component (which required nexus-staging-maven-plugin) earlier. I suppose with this change to remove - nexus-staging-maven-plugin, we can manage blueprint-generator as sub-module. \n\nHowever there is another repo (dcaegen2/services) which also has dependency on subproject and versioning. We cannot move the version to root as each sub-component will have independent release versioning. For this case global-jjb may be required to be adapted to support different version properties path. Can this be supported?",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "13e7cb8bfc84ba709a5e2f38b1268cde65ff6f4f",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 481,
          "name": "Jessica Wagantall",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jwagantall@linuxfoundation.org",
          "username": "jwagantall"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-06-14 18:17:23.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nLet me check.. i think i can be possible... \nLet me work on a change in global-jjb and ask my team for their opinion",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "c67c3e9206f3f7423bac66cc9aa53bfa753d85a6",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 93,
          "name": "Vijay Venkatesh Kumar",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "vijayv81@gmail.com",
          "username": "vv770d"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-06-14 22:48:42.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nokay, thanks Jess.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
